OL,3,CIs the treasury hinting at tax rise
OL,4,Cwiggle room?
OL,6,FDarren Jones, chief secretary to the
OL,7,FTreasury, is a fastidious minister who
OL,8,Fchooses his words carefully. So I was
OL,9,Fstruck by what he said Monday morning
OL,10,Fabout the pledges on tax his party
OL,11,Fmade in its 2024 election manifesto.
OL,13,FHe said the promise meant: "Not
OL,14,Fincreasing the headline rate of income
OL,15,Ftax or employee national insurance and
OL,16,Fnot to increase the headline rate of
OL,17,FVAT. That was a very clear promise
OL,18,Fcoming into the election."
OL,20,FThe thing is that's not what the
OL,21,Fmanifesto says. These are its words:
