OL,3,CIs the treasury hinting at tax rise
OL,4,Cwiggle room?
OL,6,FThe question is what Jones means by
OL,7,Fthe "headline rate". Does he just mean
OL,8,Fthe 20% most of us are conscious of
OL,9,Fbecause it applies to so many items,
OL,10,For is he also referring to the 0% on
OL,11,Ffood and the 5% on energy (there are
OL,12,Falso other lesser categories where the
OL,13,Frates are 5% or nil)?
OL,15,FThe point is that the chancellor could
OL,16,Fcut the main rate of VAT to, say 18%,
OL,17,Fand raise that kind of money by
OL,18,Feliminating the vast categories of our
OL,19,Fspending that incur nil or 5% VAT.
