OL,3,CIs the treasury hinting at tax rise
OL,4,Cwiggle room?
OL,6,FBut it is striking that Jones' words
OL,7,Fwere about the headline rate
OL,8,F(singular) of VAT, rather than ruling
OL,9,Fout an increase in the scope and
OL,10,Fburden. He also made the distinction
OL,11,Fthat Labour's working people's pledge
OL,12,Fin the manifesto relates to
OL,13,F"payslips", not indirect taxes like
OL,14,FVAT.
OL,16,FAll of which means such a VAT rise is
OL,17,Fin play, unless and until Jones,
OL,18,FReeves, or Starmer tell us otherwise.
